The Chronicle Mbulelo Mpofu, Showbiz Reporter
Music lovers in Gwanda are in for a rare treat as urban grooves artiste, ExQ who is riding high with his Verified Milestone album, will be in the mining town this Saturday. This will be his first time performing there at a show that has been scheduled to take place at Phoenix Shisanyama. After successfully launching Verified Milestone which contains hit Nezvangu recently, ExQ will keep the spirit of love alive as he performs at an event that has been dubbed “Love Is in The Air”. Event organisers said it is all systems go.  Said Phoenix Shisanyama’s general manager, Farai Chemura: “We’re prepared with tickets already being sold. It’s all systems go and revellers should expect to have quality time with family, friends, and colleagues as we welcome Valentine’s Day with song and dance.” Mr Putiti as ExQ is affectionately known will be backed by DJs who include Wyqlif, T Money, Prince Eskhosini and Slimza. Over the years, ExQ has been known for releasing love songs that have gone on to become national favourites. Some of the yesteryear and recent love hit songs from him include Try ft Ammara Brown, Musikanzwa, Bhachura, Wakatemba, Ndokutevera, Hauchambofona and Marizudo. – @eMKlass_49.